    <h3 class="subtitle">Tools:</h3>
    <p>Glue, Scissors, Glue Gun, Tape</p>

    <h3 class="subtitle">Materials:</h3>
    <p>Cardboard, Brown wrapping paper, Gray wrapping paper, 3 food containers</p>

    <h3 class="subtitle">Steps:</h3>
    <ol>
        <li>1. Cut the cardboard into 6 pieces with the size 67 cm x 4 cm</li><li>2. Glue each of the 3 pieces on top of each other into 2 stacked pieces (Part A)</li><li>3. Cut another new cardboard into 12 pieces with the size 41 cm x 4 cm</li><li>4. Glue each of the 3 pieces on top of each other into 4 stacked pieces (Part B)</li><li>5. Glue the 2 Part B pieces to the edge of Part A and tape it</li><li>6. Cover Part B with brown paper</li><li>7. Cut another new cardboard into 16 pieces with the size 2 cm x 69 cm</li><li>8. Glue each of the 2 pieces on top of each other into 8 stacked pieces (Part C)</li><li>9. Cover Part C with gray paper</li><li>10. Cut another new cardboard into 16 pieces with the size 2 cm x 27 cm</li><li>11. Glue each of the 2 pieces on top of each other into 8 stacked pieces (Part D)</li><li>12. Cover Part D with brown paper</li><li>13. Glue Part C to Part D 3cm downwards from the edge and use a push pin under it, then glue gun the push pin (Part E)</li><li>14. Repeat steps 13 for the other 3 sticks</li><li>15. Glue Part A and one Part B to make a 'c' shaped piece</li><li>16. Glue the 'c' shaped piece to Part E</li><li>17. Use 3 food containers as a base and put Part E on top of it</li><li>18. Cut another new cardboard into 12 pieces with the size 3 cm x 40 cm</li><li>19. Fold all of them circularly and tape the end (Part F)</li><li>20. Cut another new cardboard into 2 pieces with the size 80 cm x 33 cm (Part G)</li><li>21. Glue all Part F pieces to all edges and the middle of Part G</li><li>22. Tape the edges of Part G</li><li>23. Cover Part G with any desired wrapping paper color</li><li>24. Glue Part G on top of the assembled parts' product</li>
    </ol>

